result.adr_address: 201, 16-20 Chater Rd, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Starbucks

reviews.text: I really like this Starbucks. Food drink and price wise this is fairly typical perhaps with a slightly better range than usual. But overall typical. Same can be said for the staff. However where this really is outstanding us in the convenience of its location and the huge amount of seating. For a spot to meet or sit and contemplate the world, whilst staying centrally located, this is truly useful.

There's so many outlets around, it's almost like it's competing amongst each other here. It's definitely more comfortable and spacious here compared to many others in crowded Hong Kong.

Since it's in Central, the crowd is a mix of tourists, expats and locals. It's a nice place to rest your legs after a long day of walking and sightseeing.

Attractive space with a good range of seating.

 Decent coffee, consistent with the brand, with some selection of teas, juices and bottled drinks. Typical selection of snacks and a counter serving more substantial food. 

The noise level is noticeably louder after the store's renovation / redesign, so it is less useful as a meeting place.

A bit dark place.
Great Air condition.
Crowded
Crowded and on some places very cold. But the coffee is always TOP.
